# Senior developer workflow

- Read `docs/README.md` and `docs/01-purpose.md` at the start of substantive tasks; read `INSTRUCTIONS.md` for active todos; update todos when priorities change.
- Prefer the smallest correct change; reuse existing patterns before adding abstractions.
- Briefly state intent (what / why / scope) before non-trivial implementation.
- Do not commit, push, or open PRs unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Before ending a session with open work: note branch name, blockers, and follow-up commands in `INSTRUCTIONS.md`.
